<item>
            <title>[LU-15039] Reference leak in lnet_parse()</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-15039</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Bug introduced by:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;commit 955080c3ae3f33c98e068f52a096761ea28624b7
Author: Chris Horn &amp;lt;chris.horn@hpe.com&amp;gt;
Date:   Fri Jul 10 12:33:50 2020 -0500

    LU-13779 lnet: Correct asymmetric route detection
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We need to drop the reference taken by lnet_nid2peerni_locked() if we&apos;re dropping the message because of detected asymmetric route. This &lt;em&gt;was&lt;/em&gt; fixed in PS4 of &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-13779&quot; title=&quot;Correct asymmetric route detection&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-13779&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-13779&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, but the fix was lost in subsequent rebases of the patch.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
